# SEQUENCE 08 — THE KING WHO WAS A BEGGAR

/* TRACE: FU-044 | SC-138 */

EXT. SAVAKA KINGDOM — IRRIGATED FIELDS / ROYAL COURT — DAY #54#

Water moves through maintained channels. Grain stores are counted. Children eat in the shade while cattle drink downstream from human access points.

Prosperity is not shown as decorative wealth. It is visible in ordinary dependence.

PUNNIYARAJAN watches from the royal balcony.

He should feel satisfaction.

Instead, he feels distance.

/* TRACE: FU-045 | SC-140 */

INT. ROYAL ARCHIVE — NIGHT #55#

Records of his birth are placed beside accounts of unusual prosperity after his arrival.

A minister explains the traditions surrounding the king's life.

JANAMITHRAN

A kingdom asks many things from a ruler.

PUNNIYARAJAN

And what does a ruler ask from himself?

JANAMITHRAN

Usually more than the kingdom can afford.

The king finds references to an earlier name.

APUTHIRAN.

/* TRACE: FU-046 | SC-141 */

INT. MANIPALLAVAM SHRINE — MEMORY / VISION #56#

Punniyarajan stands before the sacred space.

Images emerge:

A child protected by a cow.

A man feeding strangers.

A bowl passing from hand to hand.

A lonely figure placing the vessel into water.

The memories do not replace him.

They challenge him.

PUNNIYARAJAN

Was I better then?

ARAVANA ADIGAL

You were responsible then.

You are responsible now.

/* TRACE: FU-047 | SC-142 */

INT. MANIPALLAVAM — CONTINUOUS #57#

Punniyarajan reaches toward the memory of Aputhiran.

He cannot touch it.

ARAVANA ADIGAL

A previous life can explain compassion.

It cannot perform your duty.

PUNNIYARAJAN

Then why remember?

ARAVANA ADIGAL

So you do not mistake power for your first life.

The king understands the difference.

/* TRACE: FU-048 | SC-143 */

EXT. SAVAKA KINGDOM — RETURN JOURNEY #58#

Punniyarajan travels back through the land he rules.

He sees:

A farmer waiting for water.

A child waiting for education.

An elder waiting for medicine.

He understands what Aputhiran never had to govern:

Systems.

/* TRACE: FU-049 | SC-144 */

INT. ROYAL COURT — DAY #59#

The king returns.

Some ministers expect renunciation.

Others expect celebration.

He offers neither.

PUNNIYARAJAN

I have remembered a life where one person carried food to the hungry.

A pause.

PUNNIYARAJAN (CONT'D)

I cannot honour that life by leaving the hungry to others.

JANAMITHRAN

Then you have understood him.

The court begins planning reform.

Not a miracle.

A responsibility.

END SEQUENCE 08